uture into the present, you can do something about it usually before it gets too late.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nBy the way, only a real man can accept his feminine side.''I don't know who fed you that line of garbage, but I can promise she's laughing at you right now.\n\n- Gena Showalter, The Darkest Seduction\n|\nPoverty frees them from ordinary standards of behaviour, just as money frees people from work.\n\n- George Orwell, Down and Out in Paris and London\n|\nused to see people in love . seeing them ,used to say -how heavenly it is ,they looks so happy in love. now i toughed by love- and don't say the same .\n\n- litymunshi\n|\nThe combination of ammonia and chloride can be lethal but I've discovered it can work miracles as long as you keep telling yourself, 'I want to love, I want to live...\n\n- David Sedaris, Barrel Fever: Stories and Essays\n|\nRespect yourself and others will come to respect you. That is true about all of us, but especially true about women. That is the meaning of honour.\n\n- Abdulrazak Gurnah, Paradise\n|\nA life without books is a thirsty life, and one without poetry is...like a life without pictures.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nIf we don't change the direction we are headed, we will end up where we are going.\n\n- Jodi Picoult, Nineteen Minutes\n|\nWe know only that in some strange and melancholy way we have become a waste land. All the same, we are not often sad.\n\n- Erich Maria Remarque, All Quiet on the Western Front\n|\nA person must earn enlightenment, Eragon. It is not handed down to you by others, regardless of how revered they be.\n\n- Christopher Paolini, Brisingr\n|\nThe writer is either a practicing recluse or a delinquent, guilt-ridden one--or both. Usually both.\n\n- Susan\n|\nLove is like a brick. You can build a house, or you can sink a dead body.\n\n- Lady\n|\nWhether your pleasing or pissing everybody off, your doing something wrong.\n\n- David\n|\nMy destination is no longer a place, rather a new way of seeing.\n\n- Marcel\n|\nNew day, new hopes, new life!!\n\n- Lailah\n|\nI don't mind foreigners. God save the queen!' he squeaked and ran.\n\n- Jeaniene Frost, Halfway to the Grave\n|\nThere’s no such thing as ruining your life. Life’s a pretty resilient thing, it turns out.\n\n- Sophie Kinsella, The Undomestic Goddess\n|\nJust as a candle cannot burn without fire, men cannot live without a spiritual life.\n\n- Budha\n|\nHead knowledge is worthless, unless accompanied by submission of the will and right action.\n\n- Fulton J. Sheen, Life of Christ\n|\nPeople are funny. They want the front of the bus, the middle of the road and the back of the church. —Mrs. Miracle\n\n- Debbie Macomber, Call Me Mrs. Miracle\n|\nIt is one thing to know what should be done, it is another to do it.\n\n- Steve Backley, The Champion in all of Us: 12 Rules for Success\n|\nGod is really only another artist. He invented the giraffe, the elephant and the cat. He has no real style, He just goes on trying other things.\n\n- Pablo\n|\nThings end. People leave. And you know what? Life goes on. Besides, if bad things didn't happen, how would you be able to feel the good ones?\n\n- Elizabeth Scott, Perfect You\n|\nA good question is always a question that helps you and me grow, no matter what the answer might be.\n\n- Alin\n|\nThey say that in the second before our death, each of us understands the real reason for our existence, and out of that moment, heaven or hell is born.\n\n- Paulo Coelho, Aleph\n|\nThe strong leader takes a chance when there is little hope,The hope that he will succeed and little chance of failure\n\n- Bluenscottish\n|\nGet used to it. Life doesn't give, it takes. Anything worth having is worth fighting for.\n\n- Diana Palmer, Donavan\n|\nThy heart had gone too far in this world, and think thou to comprehend the way of the most High?\n\n- Compton\n|\nTo attain the wisdom of every season, you must live all the seasons!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nYour calling may seem insignificant to you, but to God it is very significant